#### Step 1 - OpenSCAD
The first step was to build a [model in OpenScad](https://github.com/bmsleight/shedshed/blob/master/shedshedshed.scad), after a couple of [iterations](https://github.com/bmsleight/shedshed) we got to a final version that should fit in to the space.  The advantage of modelling the shed in OpenSCAD is that I can 3D-Print some useful parts.

#### Printed Scaled-down Shed
The first useful part I can print is a model of the shed its self. 
