#### Printed Parts
The first item is a [wedge](https://github.com/bmsleight/shedshed/blob/master/wedge.scad) that is the exact angle needed for the roof beam. This can be screwed on to a piece of timber using the two wings. Which then gives suitable points to drill and install screw for connecting the roof to the frame. Also OpenSCAD makes it easy to [design](https://github.com/bmsleight/shedshed/blob/master/hole_template.scad) and print a hole template for the timber. This makes it easy for me to drill holes for the screws. The last item is a simple joint to keep the timber stud work square.
